Interface for required functionality in the ERC721 standard
 for non-fungible tokens.
 Author: Nadav Hollander (nadav at dharma.io)
 https://github.com/dharmaprotocol/NonFungibleToken/blob/master/contracts/ERC721.sol

Interface for required functionality in the ERC721 standard
 for non-fungible tokens.
 Author: Nadav Hollander (nadav at dharma.io)
 https://github.com/dharmaprotocol/NonFungibleToken/blob/master/contracts/ERC721.sol

params._to: The address to be granted transfer approval. Pass address(0) to  clear all approvals.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.
The ID of the token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

params._to: The address of the recipient, can be a user or contract.
params._tokenId: The ID of the token to transfer.

params._from: The address for the token to be transferred from.
params._to: The address for the token to be transferred to.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Token that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Grant another address the right to transfer token via takeOwnership() and transferFrom()

balanceOf(address).notice: For querying balance of a particular account.

takeOwnership(uint256).notice: Allow pre-approved user to take ownership of a token.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Owner initates the transfer of the token to another account.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Third-party initiates transfer of token from address _from to address _to.
